            . I am the son of Robert Anderson; he <rs id="t18310630-220-viclabel1159" type="occupation">keeps the Antelope, in Frith-street, Holywell-mount</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-220-victim1657 t18310630-220-viclabel1159"></join>. On the evening of the 5th of June I was going home with my sister; the prisoner followed me for about three minutes, then took off my cap, and ran down <placeName id="t18310630-220-crimeloc1160">Thrawl-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-220-crimeloc1160" type="placeName" value="Thrawl-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-220-crimeloc1160" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-220-off1157 t18310630-220-crimeloc1160"></join> - I pursued, and cried, Stop thief! I caught him at the end of a court and asked him for my cap; he said he had not got it - a girl came down the court, and she said, "Halloo! Jack, is that you?" I did not see the cap - I do not know whether he gave it to her or threw it over the pales; I am quite sure he took it.</p>

               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did you lose sight of me? A. No.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-220-person1661">
                  EDWARD 
                  PARKER
               <interp inst="t18310630-220-person1661" type="surname" value="PARKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-220-person1661" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-220-person1661" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in the street. I saw the prisoner follow this lad two or three minutes - I kept my eyes upon him, and saw him take the cap off, put it under his arm, and run off; the young gentleman ran after him - he stopped at a court; I saw a girl come out and speak to the prisoner - she said, "Halloo! Jack, is that you?" he said Yes - the Policeman took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-220-person1662">
                  JAMES 
                  WALTON
               <interp inst="t18310630-220-person1662" type="surname" value="WALTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-220-person1662" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-220-person1662" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-constable. I heard the alarm, and saw the prisoner running down the street towards me; when I got up the young gentleman had him by the skirt of his coat - the cap has not been found.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going home, and this young gentleman came and said I had his cap - I said, "You are mistaken, I have nothing but my own cap;" I have no friends to take care of me.</p>
